   Description :

   LOCATION:     Pueblo, CO

   PRIMARY FUNCTION:

   Maintains and installs system protection devices, relays, RTU’s, and
   metering in Substations and Power Plants. Must be knowledgeable with
   electro-mechanical and electronic controls systems.

   REPORTING RELATIONSHIP:     Manager Substation Maintenance and
   Construction

   ESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS:
     * Setting and testing of solid state, micro-processor and
       electro-mechanical relays for protective devices used in
       substations and generation operations.
     * Setting and checking for proper levels of voltage regulation of
       LTC’s, regulators and capacitor controls.
     * Maintenance of RTU’s dealing with remote control and proper
       indication or system operation center.
     * Set and test recloser controls.
     * Maintaining and testing of substation metering and pool metering.

   ADDITIONAL RESPONSIBILITIES:
     * Testing various power-line carrier communications systems.
     * Perform system switching.
     * Wiring of Substation instrument transformers, relays, panels and
       breakers.
     * Substation equipment commissioning and acceptance testing.
     * Work with engineering personnel during testing and troubleshooting.

   WORKING RELATIONSHIPS:
     * Must be able to work with minimal supervision.

   EXPERIENCE:
     * Must possess solid state electronics background.

   EDUCATION:
     * Must remain current on all technologies introduced by the
       department in the area of responsibility.

   KNOWLEDGE:
     * Proficient in trouble shooting of system protection problems and
       schemes.

   SKILLS/ABILITY/OTHER CHARACTERISTICS:
     * Must possess strong verbal and written communication skills.
     * Must possess sufficient computer skills.
     * Must have organizational and record keeping skills.
     * Must possess schematic reading and diagnostic skills.

   CERTIFICATIONS/CREDENTIALS:
     * Ability to attain and hold a valid Colorado CDL Class “A” Driver’s
       license in 90 days.

   SPECIAL REQUIREMENTS:
     * This position may also include some travel.

   PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS:

   You must be able to perform the requirements of this position, with or
   without a reasonable accommodation.
     * Must be able to lift 50 pounds.
     * Must be able to work outside, in weather and temperature extremes,
       for extended periods of time.

